cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with formal verification of higher-order pushdown systems using logic-based techniques such as mu-calculus model-checking. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with modelling higher-order programs using pushdown systems. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with regular sets of configurations and their computability. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper deals with the use of higher-order stacks in pushdown systems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the computation of winning regions in reachability games, which can be related to game-theoretic approaches in machine learning.
